Rio de Janeiro's 3,500dockworkers went on strike for an indefinite period today todemand wage increases, a spokesman for the dockers said.    The Rio dockers did not get support from their colleaguesin Santos, Brazil's main port, but the spokesman said theywould not return to work unless their demands were met.    Earlier this week, some 65,000 dockworkers cancelled ascheduled national strike to pressure port officials to givethem a wage increase and other benefits.    A Rio port spokesman said the halt would cause daily lossesof about 100,000 U.S. Dlrs. Reuter&#3;